narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to apply things we learned to more difficult problem solving tasks.
Integral calculus, increased quantitative fluency, series, and parametric equations.
I developed a greater appreciation for calculus through this course. Course material was packaged very succinctly and in a manner that made all concepts seem manageable.
calc II of one variable function.
I learned about integrals, series, revolved areas, etc.
A more thorough understanding of calculus II concepts, such as integration and series.
Through this class I gained skills in calculus including integration, areas, and volume.
I learned how to integrate anti derivatives, determine whether a series converges or diverges, and use various applications of integrals.
Integrals, series, parametric curves (very pretty), polar coordinates, and other related concepts

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I thought this was a great class.
This class was fun. The exams are short and so if you can't answer one problem on one test, as happened to me, you receive a low grade (B-) on the exam. This forced me to CDF the class.
I did not entirely find the pre-class assignments useful as we reviewed the same information in class.
very good teaching, very organized course.

I thought this class did a good job teaching the content it was meant to teach. I think this can depend a lot on the professor you have since it's a smaller class setting. One of the weaknesses for me was the explorations that were due before each class. Before class, we had to submit 1 or 2 short quizes that were meant to give an introduction to the material in the class. I honestly felt that they were useless and I would usually just submit the quiz as many times as I needed to get full marks.

Strengths: very structured and organized. Allows students to improve throughout the course by offering options for weighing midterms and finals.

Weaknesses: not much.
This course went very fast, it would have been beneficial to have access to recording of the class to review after the class. However, the resources for help were good and helpful.
I really enjoyed the guided worksheets and the Canvas pre-class activities. I feel that these class materials really supplemented the in class learning!

The course is very thorough and there are many resources to aid learning. There are lectures, worksheets, explorations, office hours, extra practice sessions, and a lot of past exams to study. I just wish we had also covered partial fractions, but time is limited and it is only a minor detail.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: For STEM majors, I would recommend this course. If you do not need to take MATH 115, I would not take it unless you genuinely enjoy math.
Yes. Fun class with intellectual challenge. Be prepared to work.
If this is a prereq requirement, it's a great math course and its very engaging!
I would recommend this course considering it provides a neatly-organized presentation of calculus 2 and builds upon calculus 1 in an orderly fashion.
yes

I wouldn't say its an easy class but I wouldn't say its too hard either since its still one of the lower level math classes. If a student needs to take math 115 for whatever reason, I would say as long as you dont hate math youll be fine, I did geniunely enjoy the class but that just depends on how much you like math.
Yes. If you took AP Calculus BC in high school and don't want to dive straight into multi-variable calculus, then take this course for a more thorough understanding of series and integrals.
Yes. This course gives a good intro to integral calculus.
Yes! Calculus II is fundamental knowledge for all sorts of majors and it is taught in an amazing way, especially by Professor Mihai.
Absolutely! Whether you need to learn this math or just want to get smarter, it will greatly develop your quantitative skills.
